<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD201FEE8F5CA" blockId="31.[189,334,889,915]" box="[189,334,889,915]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="530C81C4FFB93521FF4FD201FEE8F5CA" bold="true" box="[189,334,889,915]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FF4FD201FEE8F5CA" bold="true" box="[189,334,889,915]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD2D5FE21F24F" blockId="31.[189,1398,940,1046]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
HABITUS. Encrusting sponge 
<quantity id="CF039B4DFFB93521FDEBD2D4FDC6F59E" box="[537,608,940,967]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
thick and 
<quantity id="CF039B4DFFB93521FD16D2D5FC96F59E" box="[740,816,941,967]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="90C02A2DFFB93521FC73D2D4FC54F59E" box="[897,1010,940,967]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 13. Scopalina cribrosa Bertolino, Costa &amp; Pansini sp. nov., holotype (CILE 32; MSGN 61498). A. The holotype in life. B. Styles. C. Magnification of the style ends." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4022427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4022427/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Surface slightly conulose with visible oscula, ostia and canal network. Slightly hispid. Colour in life reddish orange (
<figureCitation id="90C02A2DFFB93521FB04D2ACFACFF5B6" box="[1270,1385,980,1007]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 13. Scopalina cribrosa Bertolino, Costa &amp; Pansini sp. nov., holotype (CILE 32; MSGN 61498). A. The holotype in life. B. Styles. C. Magnification of the style ends." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4022427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4022427/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Consistency soft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD53AFBB3F2DC" blockId="31.[189,1399,1090,1157]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">SKELETON. Choanosomal skeleton consisting of bundles of thin styles entirely enclosed in spongin. Dendritic fibres rising up from basal spongin plate. Low spicular density.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD5C8FB0DF2AB" blockId="31.[189,1398,1200,1267]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
SPICULES. Megascleres: Smooth styles, bent near the head, ending with tip not pointed but almost rounded (
<figureCitation id="90C02A2DFFB93521FEDFD5A0FE26F2AB" box="[301,384,1240,1266]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[189,1398,265,1878]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 13. Scopalina cribrosa Bertolino, Costa &amp; Pansini sp. nov., holotype (CILE 32; MSGN 61498). A. The holotype in life. B. Styles. C. Magnification of the style ends." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4022427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4022427/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
B–C), 520–(1616.15)–2091 μm long and 2.5–(23.25)–32.5 μm thick.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD466FEBBF361" blockId="31.[189,285,1310,1336]" box="[189,285,1310,1336]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="530C81C4FFB93521FF4FD466FEBBF361" bold="true" box="[189,285,1310,1336]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FF4FD466FEBBF361" bold="true" box="[189,285,1310,1336]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD429FBE3F332" blockId="31.[189,1093,1361,1388]" box="[189,1093,1361,1388]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Species lives at a depth of 
<quantity id="CF039B4DFFB93521FE04D42AFD95F335" box="[502,563,1362,1388]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
, on a rocky slope covered by coralline algae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40E16523FFB93521FF4FD4E0FC6AF1B2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD4E0FE89F3EB" blockId="31.[189,303,1432,1458]" box="[189,303,1432,1458]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="530C81C4FFB93521FF4FD4E0FE89F3EB" bold="true" box="[189,303,1432,1458]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FF4FD4E0FE89F3EB" bold="true" box="[189,303,1432,1458]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="084436A8FFB93521FF4FD4B3FC6AF1B2" blockId="31.[189,1399,1483,2027]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
From five species of the 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FE2CD4B3FDF5F3BC" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[478,595,1483,1509]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FE2CD4B3FDF5F3BC" box="[478,595,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus known in the Southern Hemisphere (
<tableCitation id="45790313FFB93521FBA7D4B3FB16F3BC" box="[1109,1200,1483,1509]" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="33.[188,257,542,571]" captionText="Table 7 (continued on the next page). Morphological characters and distribution of the species of Scopalina Schmidt, 1862. The distribution refers to that present in the World Porifera Database (van Soest et al. 2020)." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Table 7</tableCitation>
), only 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FAF3D4B3FCA3F054" authority="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle, 2011" authorityName="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle" authorityYear="2011" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bunkeri">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FAF3D4B3FEB1F055" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina bunkeri</emphasis>
Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle, 2011
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from Chilean coast by 
<bibRefCitation id="6C6A4B59FFB93521FAFAD48AFEF6F06C" author="Bertolino" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bertolino" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="306 - 320" refId="ref15474" refString="Bertolino M., Costa G., Reboa A., Bavestrello G., Pansini M., Betti F., Marzia Bo. &amp; Daneri G. 2019. The sponge fauna of the Seno Magdalena and Puyuhuapi Fjord (Chile), with a description of two new species. Zootaxa 4623 (2): 306 - 320. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4623.2.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Bertolino 
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FF4FD763FF51F06D" box="[189,247,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FD43D763FC81F06D" authorityName="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle" authorityYear="2011" box="[689,807,1562,1589]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bunkeri">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FD43D763FC81F06D" box="[689,807,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. bunkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a very spiky surface and by the presence of smaller styles (
<tableCitation id="45790313FFB93521FE64D73AFE52F004" box="[406,500,1602,1629]" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="33.[188,257,542,571]" captionText="Table 7 (continued on the next page). Morphological characters and distribution of the species of Scopalina Schmidt, 1862. The distribution refers to that present in the World Porifera Database (van Soest et al. 2020)." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Table 7</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FDFCD73AFD56F005" authority="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri, 2020" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" box="[526,752,1602,1628]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FDFCD73AFD56F005" box="[526,752,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21BC57C1FFB93521FD08D73BFCFEF004" box="[762,856,1603,1629]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FC09D73BFEA7F0DD" authority="(Pulitzer-Finali, 1982)" baseAuthorityName="Pulitzer-Finali" baseAuthorityYear="1982" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Axinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="australiensis">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FC09D73BFB14F005" box="[1019,1202,1602,1629]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. australiensis</emphasis>
(Pulitzer-Finali, 1982)
</taxonomicName>
from Eastern 
<collectingCountry id="70EC7638FFB93521FE5BD712FDB3F0DD" box="[425,533,1642,1668]" name="Australia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Australia</collectingCountry>
in its external morphology, having an erect habit, large body and spicule size, but much smaller styles (
<tableCitation id="45790313FFB93521FDEBD7EAFDD5F0F4" box="[537,627,1682,1709]" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="33.[188,257,542,571]" captionText="Table 7 (continued on the next page). Morphological characters and distribution of the species of Scopalina Schmidt, 1862. The distribution refers to that present in the World Porifera Database (van Soest et al. 2020)." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Table 7</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FD7AD7EAFCC0F0F5" authority="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri, 2020" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" box="[648,870,1682,1708]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FD7AD7EAFCC0F0F5" box="[648,870,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21BC57C1FFB93521FC9FD7EBFC61F0F4" box="[877,967,1683,1709]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FBAFD7EAFDBCF08D" authority="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle, 2011" authorityName="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle" authorityYear="2011" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FBAFD7EAFB5DF0F5" box="[1117,1275,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. erubescens</emphasis>
Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle, 2011
</taxonomicName>
from the Falklands / 
<collectingCountry id="70EC7638FFB93521FCE2D7C2FCDBF08D" box="[784,893,1722,1748]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Malvinas</collectingCountry>
in its pale pink colour, a conulose surface, and styles that are four times shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FCE1D79AFC15F0A5" authorityName="Goodwin, Jones, Neely &amp; Brickle" authorityYear="2011" box="[787,947,1762,1788]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FCE1D79AFC15F0A5" box="[787,947,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="45790313FFB93521FC30D79AFBB8F0A5" box="[962,1054,1762,1788]" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="33.[188,257,542,571]" captionText="Table 7 (continued on the next page). Morphological characters and distribution of the species of Scopalina Schmidt, 1862. The distribution refers to that present in the World Porifera Database (van Soest et al. 2020)." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Table 7</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FBC7D79AFAB2F0A5" authority="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri, 2020" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" box="[1077,1300,1762,1788]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FBC7D79AFAB2F0A5" box="[1077,1300,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21BC57C1FFB93521FAEED79AFAD1F0A5" box="[1308,1399,1762,1788]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FEA5D672FC7EF17D" authority="(Hooper, Cook, Hobbs &amp; Kennedy, 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Hooper, Cook, Hobbs &amp; Kennedy" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[343,984,1801,1828]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hapalia">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FEA5D672FE77F17A" box="[343,465,1801,1828]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. hapalia</emphasis>
(Hooper, Cook, Hobbs &amp; Kennedy, 1997)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70EC7638FFB93521FBD4D671FB34F17A" box="[1062,1170,1801,1827]" name="Australia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Australia</collectingCountry>
both in the colour and the presence of strongyles, which are lacking in the new species. Finally, regarding species of the Southern Hemisphere, 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FE38D622FDEFF12A" authority="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri, 2020" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" box="[458,585,1881,1908]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FE38D622FDEFF12A" box="[458,585,1881,1908]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21BC57C1FFB93521FDA3D622FD0DF12D" box="[593,683,1882,1908]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FCB6D622FB63F12A" authority="(Lendenfeld, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Lendenfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[836,1221,1881,1908]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="incrustans">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FCB6D622FC7DF12A" box="[836,987,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. incrustans</emphasis>
(Lendenfeld, 1887)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70EC7638FFB93521FAF9D621FAD1F12A" box="[1291,1399,1881,1907]" name="Australia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Australia</collectingCountry>
by its larger styles. The nine species of 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FD64D6F9FCADF1C2" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[662,779,1921,1947]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FD64D6F9FCADF1C2" box="[662,779,1921,1947]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported from the Northern Hemisphere differ from 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FF4FD6D1FE9CF19A" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,314,1961,1987]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FF4FD6D1FE9CF19A" box="[189,314,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the size of spicules, and often in their shape (
<tableCitation id="45790313FFB93521FCAAD6D1FC17F19D" box="[856,945,1961,1988]" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="33.[188,257,542,571]" captionText="Table 7 (continued on the next page). Morphological characters and distribution of the species of Scopalina Schmidt, 1862. The distribution refers to that present in the World Porifera Database (van Soest et al. 2020)." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Table 7</tableCitation>
). We, therefore, propose that 
<taxonomicName id="CFFB4D2BFFB93521FAF3D6D1FEB9F1B2" authority="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri, 2020" authorityName="Bertolino &amp; Costa &amp; Bavestrello &amp; Pansini &amp; Daneri" authorityYear="2020" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribrosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A8FEABAFFB93521FAF3D6D1FEB9F1B2" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scopalina cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21BC57C1FFB93521FED5D6A9FE27F1B2" box="[295,385,2001,2027]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
should be considered as a species new to science.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
